                                 USBWall

----------- Requirements before installing -----------

Get kernel sources : kernel.org or distributor's kernels sources package
Developed with 
   > Linux Kernel : version 2.6.32-34
   > Distribution : Ubuntu 10.04 LTS (Lucid Lynx) 

----------- Installation -----------
0- Open a linux console

1- Compile the module :
	> go to the "usball" repertory : cd .../usbwall
        > run the conpilation : make

2- Insert the module (whit root permission) :
        > go to the "src" repertory : cd .../usbwall/src
        > insert the module : insmod usbwall.ko

3- To see usbwall kernel messages 
        > use : dmesg | grep usbwall  

4- To remove the usb_storage module (whit root permission) :
	> rmmod usb_storage

5- To remove the usbwall module (whit root permission) :
	> rmmod usbwall 


